metadata.value: Archibald Pitcairne was a university professor at the University of Leiden where he taught medicine to many of the prestigious doctors of the time. Besides his position at the university, Pitcairne was known as an outspoken bibliophile and held on the most impressive private libraries while he was alive. This manuscript holds both a poem as well as a catalogue of his extensive collection, written in Latin and composed with multiple sizes of papers.
